Text: ' His father was '
Reference: Hermann Einstein ''
Text: ', a salesman and engineer. His mother was '
Reference: Einstein family#Pauline Koch 'Pauline Einstein (née Koch)'
Text: '. In 1880, the family moved to '
Reference: Munich ''
Text: ', where his father and his uncle founded ''Elektrotechnische Fabrik J. Einstein & Cie'', a company that manufactured electrical equipment based on '
Reference: direct current ''
Text: '.'
Inline Tag: ref attributes: [name : 'Bio']
Text: '

The Einsteins were non-observant Jews. Albert attended a '
Reference: Catholic school 'Catholic elementary school'
Text: ' from the age of five for three years. Later, at the age of eight, Einstein was transferred to the '
Reference: Luitpold Gymnasium ''
Text: ' where he received advanced primary and secondary school education until he left Germany seven years later.'
